//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Build Ignore
//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

// This file defines the file paths (or partial paths wildcarded with a *) to resources which should not be overwritten
// by our build post process.
// By default, any match will result in a full ignore. However, if an entry in this file begins with a tilde (~), this
// denotes a partial ignore, which only ignores the file if (a version of) it has already been copied over. If the file
// doesn't already exist, it will be copied.

*.gitignore